WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.960
And I'm going to be discussing, so sorovatamig, as you know, is not yet approved, but I'm going

00:00:05.960 --> 00:00:13.800
to be presenting the first in human data. And my apology, one of my slides got flipped. Yeah.

00:00:14.220 --> 00:00:20.780
So sorovatamig is a CD19 Bispecific. And as we know, the currently approved bispecifics

00:00:20.780 --> 00:00:27.200
are mostly CD20. And there's a huge unmet need for other targets for bispecifics,

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:33.200
not only in lymphoma, but also in ALL, where we currently have blenatumab, which, as you know,

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:40.500
is like a continuous infusion. So sorovatamig is a CD19 bispecific. It's designed in such a way

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:50.400
that the CD19 binding site has high affinity to the B cells, but the CD3 binding site has a lower

00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:56.660
affinity. Theoretically, you know, that the purpose was to reduce the CRS incidence.

00:00:57.200 --> 00:01:01.920
So this is, this was a basket trial, included a lot of types of lymphomas. We're going to be

00:01:01.920 --> 00:01:07.080
focusing on the follicular lymphoma and diffuse large B cell lymphoma today. The way that it's

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:12.900
administered, it's intravenous. During cycle one, there's a step-up dosing. It went through many

00:01:12.900 --> 00:01:17.740
iterations. This is the double step-up dosing. But right now, there's also, we're also developing a

00:01:17.740 --> 00:01:25.160
three-step-up dosing approach to, again, mitigate some of the toxicities. After the ramp-up for

00:01:25.160 --> 00:01:27.120
cycle one, patients get it every two weeks.

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:32.740
And for those who achieve a CR after cycle six, and they, they, they have at least two imaging

00:01:32.740 --> 00:01:38.780
showing CR, they could go to once a monthly treatment for a total of up to two years. So

00:01:38.780 --> 00:01:46.460
this is also a time-limited therapy. And so this is the diffuse large B cell lymphoma cohort. And

00:01:46.460 --> 00:01:52.500
again, you know, these are just the inclusion and the, you know, the key eligibility criteria.

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:57.180
There's MRD built into the study as well. Patients, you know,

00:01:57.200 --> 00:02:01.580
who are enrolled were, had at least two prior lines of therapy. So this is the diffuse large

00:02:01.580 --> 00:02:05.600
B cell lymphoma cohort. And you could look at the demographics. This is a very high risk

00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:11.740
group of patients. The study was really very inclusive. So it enrolled patients who had

00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:18.500
prior exposure to CAR-T cell therapy, CD2 at 20 bispecifics, bulky disease, double-hit lymphoma,

00:02:18.660 --> 00:02:23.620
refractory disease. And you could see here that there were some patients who were CD20 negative,

00:02:23.620 --> 00:02:27.020
and these patients, you know, may not respond to the currently approved

00:02:27.200 --> 00:02:32.400
CD20 bispecifics, for example. The lines of therapy with the median was three, but you could

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:40.340
see here, some patients had up to 13 lines of therapy. The, if you look at the prior treatments,

00:02:40.480 --> 00:02:46.460
again, almost half of the, half of these patients had failed prior CAR-T cell therapy. Two patients

00:02:46.460 --> 00:02:55.520
had an allo. There were 15% of patients had prior bispecifics, CD20 bispecific. So this is the

00:02:55.520 --> 00:02:56.580
efficacy in the diffuse large B cell lymphoma cohort. And again, this is the efficacy in the

00:02:56.580 --> 00:03:02.120
diffuse large B cell lymphoma cohort. And, you know, these are the different dose levels. And

00:03:02.120 --> 00:03:08.880
you could clearly see there is, you know, higher responses with higher dose levels. The final

00:03:08.880 --> 00:03:13.720
dose level that we're going to go for, for the phase two trial is the 25 milligrams. So far,

00:03:13.780 --> 00:03:20.480
the overall response is 77% with a CR rate of 54%. Again, this is a single agent. There is also MRD

00:03:20.840 --> 00:03:26.200
built in. The patients who do achieve a CR, you could clearly see that those

00:03:26.200 --> 00:03:31.980
responses can be durable. And obviously we need longer follow-up to, to clarify that.

00:03:32.840 --> 00:03:41.660
In terms of MRD, so of the 25, of the 29 patients who had CR, the majority of them were MRD negative,

00:03:41.900 --> 00:03:49.020
so 90%. And you could clearly see from the, the swimmer's plot here that patients achieve MRD

00:03:49.020 --> 00:03:53.700
negativity on average, you know, close to two months or so. So again, if it works, it works

00:03:53.700 --> 00:03:58.980
quickly and these responses can be durable. This is just one example for a patient. And again,

00:03:59.020 --> 00:04:02.500
you know, we all see these patients in clinic who have failed CAR-T cell therapy or failed

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:06.860
a CD20 by specific. And unfortunately, you know, these patients had typically have low responses.

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:12.200
This is a patient who had third line epitomab and you could clearly see that, you know,

00:04:12.400 --> 00:04:16.280
they had an excellent response here. It's not just this patient. We all have like a lot of

00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:23.320
other patients on the study as well. Toxicity wise. So the CRS and the diffuse large B cell lymphoma cohort was

00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:30.980
seen evenly during the step-up dosing. However, so the total CRS was, was seen in half of, half of

00:04:30.980 --> 00:04:37.460
the patients. The vast majority of these were grade one, 42%, with 6% having grade two. So

00:04:37.460 --> 00:04:45.800
those typically, you know, happen within 24 hours, sometimes 48 hours. It typically lasts for about a

00:04:45.800 --> 00:04:52.320
day. The vast majority of patients, it subsides spontaneously. The use of tusolucumab here on the

00:04:52.320 --> 00:04:52.940
study was, was 29%.

00:04:52.940 --> 00:05:03.420
And 3% received steroids. In terms of ICANNs, so ICANNs was, the overall was 27%. There were some patients, a few

00:05:03.420 --> 00:05:09.680
patients who had a grade three ICANNs, 8%, but the rest were mostly grade one and two. And again,

00:05:09.720 --> 00:05:14.220
the ICANNs here with these bispecifics, it's typically something that happens the next day

00:05:14.220 --> 00:05:22.640
or the day after. A lot of those included confusion, aphasia, disorientation, and it

00:05:22.640 --> 00:05:28.120
typically lasts about a day. We usually start those patients on steroid, and it usually resolves

00:05:28.120 --> 00:05:33.980
on its own. And again, this is still a moving target because the, the, the ramp-up dosing has

00:05:33.980 --> 00:05:38.840
been, is still, you know, modified, and we're now going to with, with a three-step-up dosing

00:05:38.840 --> 00:05:46.600
approach. In terms of the follicular lymphoma cohort, now the, we had 61 patients here,

00:05:47.340 --> 00:05:52.500
and you could see the, you know, the, the demographics here. So 36% of patients had POT24,

00:05:52.500 --> 00:06:00.000
these are high-risk patients. 11% had failed prior CAR-T, 8% had failed prior Bispecific.

00:06:00.720 --> 00:06:07.620
The efficacy is very, very, very promising in follicular lymphoma. So the, at the 15 milligram

00:06:07.620 --> 00:06:15.440
dose and at the 7.2 milligram dose, you could see here very high response rates, 96% with a CR rate

00:06:15.440 --> 00:06:22.320
of 92% overall. And if you look here, so the, the, these, this is the MRD,

00:06:22.360 --> 00:06:27.880
so of the patients who have MRD-evaluable data, the MRD, by the way, was done with a clarity assay.

00:06:28.740 --> 00:06:35.560
So 95% of patients who are MRD-eligible and they were in CR had detectable MRD. So again,

00:06:35.640 --> 00:06:39.620
very promising. And as you, as you can see, you know, from the swimmer's spot,

00:06:39.860 --> 00:06:44.940
these MRD negativity, they, they, they happen really early on. So the dose that's currently

00:06:44.940 --> 00:06:52.180
moving forward in the phase two trial is the 7.2 milligrams for the follicular lymphoma. In terms

00:06:52.180 --> 00:06:52.220
of the MRD-evaluable data, the MRD-evaluable data, the MRD, by the way, was done with a clarity assay.

00:06:52.220 --> 00:06:57.740
In terms of adverse events, so obviously you have, you know, a lot of these by adverse events that

00:06:57.740 --> 00:07:02.700
you could see with, with bispecifics, including some cytopenias, sometimes infections. But the

00:07:02.700 --> 00:07:10.480
CRS rates were, you know, for follicular lymphoma, overall was half of the patients, but these were

00:07:10.480 --> 00:07:17.040
mostly grade one, so mostly fevers. And again, typically happen within a day or two. The ICANS

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:21.860
in the follicular lymphoma cohort was, was low compared to the diffuse large vessel lymphoma

00:07:21.860 --> 00:07:28.920
cohort at, at 5%. And again, you know, mostly there's just two patients, one had grade one,

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:33.000
another had grade two. And as I mentioned, these are typically reversible within, within a day.

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:40.540
Next step, so it's being looked at now in, in, in a lot of, you know, other trials ongoing. So the

00:07:40.540 --> 00:07:47.920
Soundtrack F1 is, is looking at, at this sorovatamib with rituximab in previously untreated

00:07:48.340 --> 00:07:51.840
follicular lymphoma in a phase three trial with a comparator arm.

00:07:51.860 --> 00:07:58.560
Chemoimmunotherapy. Soundtrack P is, is a phase two registrational looking at follicular lymphoma

00:07:58.560 --> 00:08:04.820
and diffuse large B cell lymphoma cohorts currently enrolling. And Soundtrack E is looking at other

00:08:04.820 --> 00:08:11.900
histologies, including CLL, mantle cell, and large cell lymphoma cohorts. There's also, I didn't show

00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:18.700
it here, there's also an ALL study going on in patients with relapsed ALL. Thank you for your

00:08:18.700 --> 00:08:18.860
attention.
